# Fix Login Failure (ERR_CONNECTION_REFUSED)

The user is testing locally on their laptop (`10.172.19.161`) before deploying to the production VM (`10.172.19.16`). The login is failing with `ERR_CONNECTION_REFUSED` because the backend is currently unresponsive on port 5000 and the configurations are targeted only at the production IP.

## Proposed Changes

### [Server]

#### [MODIFY] [.env](file:///c:/Apps/Leave%20Tracker/server/.env)
- Update `ALLOWED_ORIGINS` to include the laptop IP `http://10.172.19.161:8080`.
- Change `NODE_ENV` to `development` to enable detailed logging and disable production-only security blocks that might be interfering with local testing.
- Ensure the server is listening correctly and responding to requests.

